  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UoA evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Intended use: pre-market submission support for a Class II centrifugal blood pump operating in CPB mode, flow range 3–6 L/min, rotational speed 2000–3500 RPM, blood viscosity modeled as Newtonian at 37 °C. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-credible-mrl2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-piv-velocity-dataset"
  ],
